C

Callback<Result> - Interface in net.markenwerk.commons.interfaces
For an arbitrary process, that will eventually yield a result, a Callback is used, to convey that result from the executor of the process (hereafter: executor) back to the initiator of the process (hereafter: initiator).

Handler<Event> - Interface in net.markenwerk.commons.interfaces
For an arbitrary process, that may encounter some kind of event and needs to delegate the event handling, a Handler is used, to convey that event from the executor of the process (hereafter: executor) back to the initiator of the process (hereafter: initiator).
